  urldate = {2025-03-30},
  abstract = {This research analyzed the 100 most popular songs (1958--1998) for artist characteristics and expression of love. In the 1990s women and black artists recorded more hits than in earlier periods. Over time, references to love in lyrics performed by women artists decreased. References to sex in lyrics peaked during 1976--1984 when women used sexual references five times more than men; however, during 1991--1998, men used more sexual references. Later songs and songs performed by white, female artists expressed greater selfishness. The quality of love expressed in lyrics remained the same. Results are discussed relative to cultural change.},
